<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>UK Energy and Climate Change Committee: Inquiry on Carbon Capture &amp; Storage, 2013</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.7pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 12pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence submitted by Zero Emissions Platform (CCS07)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">Founded in 2005, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">the Zero Emissions Platform (ZEP) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">serves as an advisor to the European Commission on the research, demonstration and deployment of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">CO</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:6.67pt; font-style:italic; vertical-align:sub">2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic"> Capture and Storage</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic"> (CCS). </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">ZEP is a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic"> coalition of over 200 members from 19 countries – representing academics, scientists, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">European </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">utilities, petroleum </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">companies, equipment suppliers and environmental NGOs</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">SUMMARY</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 27.45pt; padding-left:8.25pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">CCS </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">is</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">not only essential to meet</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">CO</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:6.67pt; vertical-align:sub">2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> reduction targets </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">cost-effectively</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">, it will </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">play a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">critical</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> role in achieving the UK’s industrialisation goals</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">By s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">timulating</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">investment</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">creating </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> preserving jobs, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">it</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">will </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">fuel economic growth</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> in both</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">power and energy-intensive industries </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">– while ensuring </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">secur</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">ity of</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> energy supply</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 27.45pt; padding-left:8.25pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">There is no question that CCS can deliver:</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> all elements of the value chain are</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> proven</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">both ZEP and UK studies agree </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">it </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">will be cost-competitiv</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">e</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> with other low-carbon </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">power options</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">post 2020.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 27.45pt; padding-left:8.25pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">However, early movers will incur significant costs</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">an uncertain environment for long-term investment</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">, which </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">will continue until the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">EU </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">ETS h</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">as</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> undergone structural reform.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> Transitional</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> support measures for CCS are therefore essential to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">cover the incremental costs of demonstration and early deployment projects</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">. </span></li></ul><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 27.45pt; padding-left:8.25pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">The UK has </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">spearheaded</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> the development of CCS </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">in Europe</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> both in terms of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">technology </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">policy</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">– </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">in particular, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">the £1 billion CCS Commercialisation Programme and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> the introduction of Feed-in Tariffs with Contracts for Difference (CfD)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">However, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">CCS </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">stands at a crossroads</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">next few years </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">will be</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">critical</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> in</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">determining</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">wh</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">ether it will be deployed </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">in time</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> to meet </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">UK and EU </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">climate targets</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">. ZEP therefore recommends</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">focus</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> on</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">the following key </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">priorities</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> so that the UK can take full advantage of its leadership role</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">:</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span></li></ul><ul type="circle" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 46.45pt; padding-left:3.2pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Continue to develop CCS CfD in order to give the industry confidence that there is a market for low-carbon electricity from CCS. This includes bankable CfDs for CCS and a transparent and predictable route to market through a CCS CfD strike price setting an</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">d allocation process. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">C</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">larity on longer-term CCS objectives and whether there is any intention to support projects beyond the current competition</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> is also needed</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">.</span></li></ul><ul type="circle" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 5pt 46.45pt; padding-left:3.2pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Continue</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> dialogue with North Sea partners </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> advance</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> essential infrastructure for CO</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:6.67pt; vertical-align:sub">2 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">transport and storage</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 5pt 46.45pt; padding-left:3.2pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Actively support efforts to r</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">emove the unreasonable – and unnecessary – burdens currently imposed on storage providers as part of the review of the CCS Directive in 2015.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 3pt 46.45pt; padding-left:3.2pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Continu</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">e</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> engage</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">ment</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> with Horizon 2020 in order to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">optimise cur</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">rent and next</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">-generation </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">echnologies</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">, drive down cost</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">enable rapid deployment post-2020. </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 9pt 13.34pt; padding-left:0.86pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">CCS will play a critical role in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">achieving</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold"> t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">he</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold"> UK’s </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">energy, climate and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">industrialisation</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold"> goals </span></li></ol><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 27.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">CO</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:6.67pt; font-weight:bold; vertical-align:sub">2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold"> reduction targets cannot be achieved </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">cost-effectively </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">without</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold"> CCS</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">:</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">just </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">10-year delay in deployment will increase the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">global </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">costs of decarbonising the power sector by $1 trillion</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">and result in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">vast </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">lost revenues for </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">producers of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">coal ($690 billion), gas ($430 billion) and oil ($230 billion)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">.</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Yet if</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> CCS develops as anticipated,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">benefits for UK</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">-based firms will total £3 to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">6.5 b</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">illion </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> year</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> as early as the late </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">2020</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">.</span><a name="_ftnref2"></a><a href="#_ftn2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27.45pt; padding-left:8.25pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">CCS clusters will create thousands of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">skilled</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold"> jobs in the UK</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> – an estimated 27,000 from 2020, rising to 70,000 by 2035</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">distributed throughout the entire economy: in engineering and manufacturing; chemical and process engineering; equipment manufacturing; pipeline design and construction; offshore exploration and injection well construction; maintenance, operation and manag</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">ement; subsurface geological characterisation; and many other specialist roles.</span><a name="_ftnref3"></a><a href="#_ftn3">[3]</a></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27.45pt; padding-left:8.25pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">CCS will </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">also </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">preserve thousands of jobs in industr</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">ies </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">beyond</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold"> power</span><a name="_ftnref4"></a><a href="#_ftn4">[4]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">– expected to account for</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> half of the global emissions cuts required by 2050 from CCS.</span><a name="_ftnref5"></a><a href="#_ftn5">[5]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Indeed, in some </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">sectors</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">such as </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">steel </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">and cement, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">CCS is the only means of achieving deep emission cuts. Energy-intensive industries</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> are the vital backbone of manufacturing value chains for both traditional and emerging technologies – including renewable energy. In the UK</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> they have a combined turnover of £95 billion, directly </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">employ</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">160,000 people in well-paid, highly skilled jobs</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> while a further 800,000</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> work in supply chains </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">across the UK</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> – including </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">iron and steelmaking, cement </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">and lime manufacture, chemicals, ceramics, glass, non-ferrous metals, pulp and paper, coke and refined petroleum product industries.</span><a name="_ftnref6"></a><a href="#_ftn6">[6]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 27.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">CO</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:6.67pt; font-weight:bold; vertical-align:sub">2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold"> transport and storage networks </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">will create</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold"> major</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold"> investment in UK infrastructure</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">, resulting in significant economies of scale</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">, especially if different CO</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:6.67pt; vertical-align:sub">2 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">sources (i.e. from power and heavy industry) are located in close proximity so they can share infras</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">tructure. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">C</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">lusters will</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">also </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">guarantee</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> work for a skilled workforce for decades to come – with the potential to export know-how from </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">such</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> projects.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> For example, the economic impact of developing the Yorkshire and Humber CO</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:6.67pt; vertical-align:sub">2 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">cluster could total £1.255 billi</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">on up to 2030; and if long-term economic benefits are also taken into account, total regional impact could amount to over £26 billion</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> by 2050</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">.</span><a name="_ftnref7"></a><a href="#_ftn7">[7]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> Early deployment of infrastructure also creates a business opportunity</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> to transport and store</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> CO</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:6.67pt; vertical-align:sub">2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> from c</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">ontinental Europe</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">.</span></li></ul><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 27.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">UK bioenergy ambitions, if combined with CCS, open the door </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">o</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">removing</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold"> CO</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:6.67pt; font-weight:bold; vertical-align:sub">2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold"> from the atmosphere</span><a name="_ftnref8"></a><a href="#_ftn8">[8]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">–</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> the only large-scale technology that can deliver net </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">negative</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> emissions</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">(</span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:normal">in addition to any emissions reductions achieved </span><span style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:normal">by replacing fossil fuels with biomass). </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">C</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">ertain biofuels production routes could provide </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">‘low-hanging fruits’ for early</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">low-cost CCS </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">deployment and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> in the U.S., Bio-CCS is already being deployed at industrial scale.</span><a name="_ftnref9"></a><a href="#_ftn9">[9]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">The</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> UK Committee on Climate Change ha</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">s </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">already </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">confirmed </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">that</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><a href="http://www.theccc.org.uk/reports/bioenergy-review" target="_blank"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:none">"It will be difficult to meet the overall 2050 emissions target unless bioenergy can account for around 10% of total UK primary ene</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:none">rgy”.</span></a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> An increase in bioenergy on such a scale would </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">therefore </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">provide ample opportunity </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">to combine</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> biomass conversion with CCS.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">CCS will </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">complement the large-scale deployment of intermittent renewable</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">energy </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">by providing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">both low-carbon baseload </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> balancing generation</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> – </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">ensuring a diverse and reliable energy supply.</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 9pt 13.34pt; padding-left:0.86pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">Transitional measures are essential to drive CCS demonstration and early deployment</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold"> </span></li></ol><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 27.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">There is no question that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">CCS </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">can deliver: all elements of the value chain are proven and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">CCS</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">has been taking place </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">successfully </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">on a small-scale </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">for over two decades</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">The </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">ZEP</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> cost reports</span><a name="_ftnref10"></a><a href="#_ftn10">[10]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">concluded that there is currently no clear difference between any of the three main capture technologies and all could be competitive once successfully demonstr</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">ated.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Among </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">storage options</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">deep saline </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">aquifers </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">hold </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">greatest storage p</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">otential, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">but</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> have generally been poorly investigated. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">The</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> ZEP cost reports </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">also </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">give confidence that post-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">demonstration</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> CCS will be cost-competitive</span><a name="_ftnref11"></a><a href="#_ftn11">[11]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">with the full ra</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">nge of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">low-carbon power options –</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">including on-/offshore wind, solar power </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">nd nuclear</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> –</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> and confirmed </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">by</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">the UK’s </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">own </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">CCS Cost Reduction Task Force</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">.</span><a name="_ftnref12"></a><a href="#_ftn12">[12]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Unlike other low-carbon technologies, CCS is at the start of the learning curve</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">, with</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> huge potenti</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">al to drive </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">costs</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> down – from both tec</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">hnology improvements </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> economies of scale. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">This </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">is why</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> confidence</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> in the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">technology </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">is so high and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">why final investment decisions have already been tak</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">en on demonstration projects </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">in the U.S., Canada and China.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 27.45pt; padding-left:8.25pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">However, e</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">arly </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">movers will</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">incur significant upfront costs, with little transport and storage infrastructure in place and an uncertain environment for long-term investment. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">I</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">n the long term, ZEP believes the EU ETS to be the most cost-efficient mechanism </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">for driving </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">deca</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">rbonisation in the EU.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">However, the price</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Emission Unit Allowances</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> (EUAs)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">has fallen to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">a level where, in the short term, it provides no incentive to invest (€2.5-5/tCO</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:6.67pt; vertical-align:sub">2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> in Q2 2013). This situation will continue until the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">EU </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">ETS has undergone structural reform – in particular setting a tighter cap out to 2030 and beyond, as part of a holistic EU </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Energy and Climate Policy </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">framework. </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 27.45pt; padding-left:8.25pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Yet even if action is taken now, it will still not result in EUA prices that are high and robust enough to deploy CCS </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">on the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> scale required</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> to meet EU climate targets</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">. Transitional</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> support measures for CCS are therefore essential to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> cover the incremental c</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">osts of demonstration and early deployment projects</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">in Europe</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">These include</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">:</span></li></ul><ul type="circle" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:10pt; list-style-position:inside; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 36pt; text-indent:-0.55pt"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">Feed-in tariffs</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">(FiTs)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">, which offer investors the greatest security of income</span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 46.45pt; padding-left:3.2pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">CCS certificates</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">could be</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> an option, if carefull</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">y designed for a defined volume</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">and ZEP has </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">offer</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">ed to advise </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">European </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Commission on the feasibility and design of such a scheme.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 46.45pt; padding-left:3.2pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Establishing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">a ‘CCS Fund’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">large enough </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">to support EU demonstration projects in both the power and industrial sectors. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Funding could come from the European Commission (e.g.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> by setting aside sufficient EUAs from the New Entrants Reserve; or earmarking funds from the EU budget, not unlike EEPR) and from Member States (e.g. by using some of the proceeds from ETS auctions, or already established national carbon taxation schemes)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">. </span></li></ul><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold; margin:0pt 0pt 9pt 13.34pt; padding-left:0.86pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">The UK must continue </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">spearhead</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold"> the development of</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold"> CCS </span></li></ol><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">The UK leads Europe in the development of CCS in two key respects: 1) it has produced six</span><a name="_ftnref13"></a><a href="#_ftn13">[13]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">robust and viable demonstration projects, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">including one in Phase II of the NER300 and 2) it will </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">introduce Feed-in T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">ariffs with CfD</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">, offering a centrally-set strike price for CCS. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">It is precisely </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">type</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> of policy </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">action </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">needed to deliver the goals set out in</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> the EU Energy Roadmap 2050, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">which</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> carries a CCS (for power) deployment rate in Europe of ~4G</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">W per year in the 2030s to ~11GW per year in the 2040s. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">This sets the pace for pre-commercial deployment from 2020 to 2030 to be ~1 GW per year in 2020 to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">~</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">3 GW per year in 2030.     </span><br /><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 9pt 27.6pt; padding-left:8.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Until recently, Europe led the world in supporting CCS, yet in the past</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> 18 months it has been unable to deliver any large-scale CCS demonstration projects – despite viable projects </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">being progressed </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">in several countries</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">It is therefore essential that the UK continues </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">to take the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">lead</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">on</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> the following </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">critical</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">issues</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">:</span></li></ul><ul type="circle" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 46.45pt; padding-left:3.2pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">Continue</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold"> to develop CCS CfD in order to give the industry confidence that there is a market for CCS</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">– early demonstration is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">vital</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> to ensure wide deployment by 2030</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">and the delivery of UK CO</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:6.67pt; vertical-align:sub">2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> reduction targets</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">. This includes </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">establishing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">bankable CfDs</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> for CCS and a transparent and predictable route to market through a CCS CfD strike price setting and allocation process. The industry also needs clarity on longer-term CCS objectives and whether there is any intention to support projects beyond the curren</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">t competition</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">.</span></li></ul><ul type="circle" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 9pt 46.45pt; padding-left:3.2pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">Continue dialogue with North Sea</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">partners and advance </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">transport and storage </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">infrastructure</span><a name="_ftnref14"></a><a href="#_ftn14">[14]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">, an issue of considerable legal and commercial complexity. However, if different CO</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:6.67pt; vertical-align:sub">2 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">sources are located in close proximity, they can share </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">infrastru</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">cture – </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">both </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">pipelines</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">nd </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">storage</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> reservoirs</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> –</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> thus benefitting significantly from economies of scale. With lead </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">tim</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">es of 6 to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">10</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> years, early strategic planning is therefore vital. This includes </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">developing effective business models;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> establishing short-term incentives for early m</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">overs</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">and establishing funding towards the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">development of CO</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:6.67pt; vertical-align:sub">2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">infrastructure</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">(transport and storage) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">in its own right, i.e. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">it</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> should not be tied to an</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:6.67pt; vertical-align:sub">y</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> given capture plant. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 9pt 46.45pt; padding-left:3.2pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">Ensure a robust regulatory framew</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">ork</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">: the ‘CCS Directive’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> (2009/31/EC)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> currently imposes unreasonable – and unnecessary – burdens, risks and uncertainties on storage providers. These should be addressed in the review of the CCS Directive in 2015, including requirements under financial liability, the transfer of responsibilit</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">y and third party access.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:10pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.45pt; padding-left:3.2pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-weight:bold">Continue engagement with Horizon 2020</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">: </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">s with all technologies, CCS will benefit from ongoing R&amp;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">D in order to further drive down costs. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">In addition to demonstration projects, the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">acceleration of</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> next-generation </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">capture </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">technologi</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">es is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">therefore </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">essential</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> to enable rapid </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">deployment post-2020</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> – in particular </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">via large-scale pilots</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">However</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">existing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">pilots</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> should </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">also </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">continue to be financed in order</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">improve</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> component performance and capture processes. They will also provide critical support to the first demonstration plants by </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">providing</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> facilities to help with the optimisation o</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">f processes and</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">demonstration of</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> operational flexibility. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">As importantly</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">, the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">y </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">will</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> also facilitate the validation of technologies for</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> use in industries </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">beyond</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> power. </span></li></ul><p style="font-size:10pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.65pt; text-indent:-14.2pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49.65pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">ZEP </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">also </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">recommends </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">establishing up to six new CO</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:6.67pt; vertical-align:sub">2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> storage pilots</span><a name="_ftnref15"></a><a href="#_ftn15">[15]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> across Europe to complement demonstration projects</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">accelerate state-of-the-art technology</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">. This </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">will </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">enable meaningful R&amp;D on a range of issues</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">which may then be used generically – on- </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">offshore. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">Qualifying and improving knowledge of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">representative</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> geological storage conditions will also greatly benefit the planning of a trans-national, European CO</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:6.67pt; vertical-align:sub">2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> transport infrastructure. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">In certain cases, the storage pilot may even be used to explore</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> industrial scale-storage in the same reservoir.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt; font-style:italic">August 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.7pt; text-indent:-17.85pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt"> “Redrawing the energy-climate map. World Energy Outlook </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">Special Report”, IEA, June 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn2"></a><a href="#_ftnref2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">AEA, 2010. Future Value of Carbon Abatement Technologies in Coal and Gas </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">Power Generation to UK Industry.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn3"></a><a href="#_ftnref3">[3]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt"> Carbon Capture and Storage Skills Study: </span><a href="http://www.apgtf-uk.com/index.php?option=com_docman&amp;task=doc_details&amp;gid=19&amp;Itemid=79"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt; text-decoration:underline">www.apgtf-uk.com/index.php?option=com_docman&amp;task=doc_details&amp;gid=19&amp;Itemid=79</span></a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><a name="_ftn4"></a><a href="#_ftnref4">[4]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt"> See ZEP’s report: CO</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:5.33pt; vertical-align:sub">2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt"> Capture and Storage (CCS) in energy-intensive industries: an indispensable route to an EU low-carbon </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">  economy”</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">: </span><a href="http://www.zeroemissionsplatform.eu/library/publication/222-ccsotherind.html"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt; text-decoration:underline">www.zeroemissionsplatfor</span><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt; text-decoration:underline">m.eu/library/publication/222-ccsotherind.html</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn5"></a><a href="#_ftnref5">[5]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt"> International Energy Agency (IEA)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn6"></a><a href="#_ftnref6">[6]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt"> </span><a href="http://www.tuc.org.uk/tucfiles/352.pdf"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt; text-decoration:underline">www.tuc.org.uk/tucfiles/352.pdf</span></a><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:10pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn7"></a><a href="#_ftnref7">[7]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt"> </span><a href="http://www.co2sense.co.uk/files/2113/5031/6058/CCS_CO2Sense_Exec_summary_FINAL.pdf"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt; text-decoration:underline">www.co2sense.co.uk/files/2113/5031/6058/CCS_CO2Sense_Exec_summary_FINAL.pdf</span></a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn8"></a><a href="#_ftnref8">[8]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">See "Biomass with CO</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:5.33pt; vertical-align:sub">2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt"> Capture and Storage (Bio-CCS) – The way forward for Europe” published by ZEP and the European  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">  Biofuels Technology Platform, 2012: </span><a href="http://www.zeroemissionsplatform.eu/library/publication/206-biomass-with-co2-capture-and-storage-bio-ccs-%20the-way-forward-for-europe.html"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt; text-decoration:underline">www.zeroemissionsplatform.eu/library/publication/206-biomass-with-co2-capture-and-storage-bio-ccs- the-way-forward-for-europe.html</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn9"></a><a href="#_ftnref9">[9]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt"> The ADM bioethanol-CCS project</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn10"></a><a href="#_ftnref10">[10]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt"> </span><a href="http://www.zeroemissionsplatform.eu/library/publication/165-zep-cost-report-summary.html"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt; text-decoration:underline">www.zeroemissionsplatform.eu/library/publication/165-zep-cost-report-summary.html</span></a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn11"></a><a href="#_ftnref11">[11]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">€</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">70-90</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">/MWh for CCS </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">with </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">coal, €70-120/MWh with gas, operating in baseload (</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">7,500 hours equivalent full load each year); </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">fuel</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">costs for hard coal and natural gas are 2.0-2.9 €/GJ and 4.5-11.0 €/GJ respectively</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn12"></a><a href="#_ftnref12">[12]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt"> </span><a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/publications/ccs-cost-reduction-task-force-final-report"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt; text-decoration:underline">www.gov.uk/government/publications/ccs-cost-reduction-task-force</span><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt; text-decoration:underline">-final-report</span></a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">   </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt">     </span></p><h3 style="background-color:#ffffff; margin:0pt; page-break-after:avoid; page-break-inside:avoid"><a name="_ftn13"></a><a href="#_ftnref13">[13]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt; font-weight:normal"> Peterhead, White Rose, Captain Clean Energy Project, Teesside Low Carbon Project, C-GEN, Don Valley  </span></h3><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn14"></a><a href="#_ftnref14">[14]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt"> See ZEP’s report, Building a CO</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:5.33pt; vertical-align:sub">2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt"> transport infrastructure for Europe”: </span><a href="http://www.zeroemissionsplatform.eu/library/publication/221-co-2transportinfra.html"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt; text-decoration:underline">www.zeroemissionsplatform.eu/library/publication/221-co-2transportinfra.html</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn15"></a><a href="#_ftnref15">[15]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt"